last_episode_to_air.name: The Cloniest Place on Earth: Missile While You Work
last_episode_to_air.overview: Joan, Abe, and the rest of the gang find themselves saddled with summer jobs at the theme park of Scudworth’s childhood dreams. Meanwhile, Candide’s plan to wipe Cloney Island off the map threatens the future of Clone High.

name: Clone High
overview: Twenty years after they were frozen, Abe, Cleo, JFK, and Joan suddenly find themselves thrust into the modern world, where they must navigate a fresh batch of historical clones, dramatic love triangles, and a formidable new foe.
tagline: One of the top clone-based high school shows on television. Period.

episodes.name: Let's Try This Again
episodes.overview: Decades after they were frozen, Abe, JFK, Joan and Cleo are suddenly thrust into 2023, where they find it difficult to navigate new societal norms.

episodes.name: Sleepover
episodes.overview: Attempting to repress her feelings for Abe, Joan finds solace in Harriet and Frida. Meanwhile, Confucius teaches JFK about the internet.

episodes.name: Anxious Times at Clone High
episodes.overview: Candide’s crisis wreaks havoc, Joan doubts her relationship with JFK, Abe turns to Frida for advice and Harriet frets over a future as a #winemom.

episodes.name: The Crown: Joancoming: It's a Cleo Cleo Cleo Cleo World
episodes.overview: When a rumor derails Cleo’s bid for homecoming queen, Joan is forced to reconsider their lifelong rivalry for the sake of the school…and the world.

episodes.name: Some Talking but Mostly Songs
episodes.overview: Hoping to land a role on hit show Tropical Hospital, Harriet stages her new musical but must contend with Joan’s creative meddling.

episodes.name: Saved by the Knoll
episodes.overview: When a fire threatens to shut down the Grassy Knoll, a desperate Abe spearheads a campaign to rebuild the town’s beloved greasy diner and save Joan.

episodes.name: Spring Broken
episodes.overview: After the clones find themselves stranded in the desert, JFK experiences a heat-induced intellectual breakthrough, Abe faces a zombie horde, and Scudworth and Mr. B hit the big-time in Vegas.

episodes.name: Sexy-Ed
episodes.overview: While Clone High mourns a power couple breakup, Candide and Scudworth hatch a plan to reunite the pair with mandatory sex education, swarthy seamen, and some sensual sax solos.

episodes.name: For Your Consideration
episodes.overview: After a fight with Scudworth, Mr. B prepares to leave Clone High for good — but not before telling Joan his epic backstory.

episodes.name: Clone Alone
episodes.overview: As Operation Spread Eagle ends, the clones face a deadly college entrance exam. Estranged from JFK, Abe, and the rest of her friends, Joan decides to fend for herself while Scudworth and Mr. B crash The Board of Shadowy Figures’ Death Maze watch party.

episodes.name: Blinded with Pseudoscience: Magnetic Distractions
episodes.overview: After returning from summer break, the students of Clone High become acquainted with their new science teacher, Professor Hirsute. Meanwhile, a newly friendless Joan receives an invite from the only club that will take her as a member.

episodes.name: Don't You Get It? Sports Are Huge in This Town
episodes.overview: Scudworth takes Frida under his wing, causing the would-be artist to consider a more lucrative career… in competitive snorkeling.

episodes.name: Bible Humpers: A Much Needed Praycation
episodes.overview: While Scudworth develops a plan to convert Clone High into a religious school, JFK seeks absolution for his philandering lifestyle from the Prayer Pals. Plagued with guilt after her tryst with Toussaint, Harriet turns to Joan – and the Lord – for advice.

episodes.name: The Principal Principle: Sub Zero to Sub Hero
episodes.overview: When Scudworth names Joan principal for the day, she tries to win her former friends back with an exclusive in-school soiree… that soon gets out of hand.

episodes.name: Money Can Buy Me Love: Stupid Is as Cupid Does
episodes.overview: As Valentine’s Day nears, Confucius and Joan con Harriet into thinking they’re a couple. Meanwhile, Scudworth swoons over an old nemesis.

episodes.name: Go Yell It on the Mountain: Snow Way Out
episodes.overview: Tensions mount on a ski trip to Avalanche Mountain, threatening love triangles, bromances… and Mr. B’s sanity.

episodes.name: Grave Mistakes: The Virgin Homicides
episodes.overview: Tasked with creating a new batch of clones, Scudworth and Mr. B realize they may be past their gravedigging prime. Then, Joan leads the charge to stop an illicit cemetery rendezvous before Abe loses everything… except his virginity.

episodes.name: Cyranos: A Portmant-Opus
episodes.overview: After Scudworth imposes mandatory Parent-Principal conferences on the student-body, Confucius enlists his feuding friends to fill in for his absentee foster parents. To win over Frida’s dad, Harriet helps give Cleo an epic make-under.

episodes.name: Cloney Island: Twist!
episodes.overview: After noticing Scudworth’s stranger-than-usual behavior, the clones uncover a tale of rival theme parks, romance, and revenge… all within the pages of his diary.

episodes.name: The Cloniest Place on Earth: Missile While You Work
episodes.overview: Joan, Abe, and the rest of the gang find themselves saddled with summer jobs at the theme park of Scudworth’s childhood dreams. Meanwhile, Candide’s plan to wipe Cloney Island off the map threatens the future of Clone High.
